This paper discusses the challenges and solutions related to wireless networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the security aspect of the proposed solution, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of blockchain technology and queuing models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of performance metrics, which is a common theme in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of queuing models and experimental validation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
